race.comment: ON POINT PIXIE (7) has more upside than most of these and will find this more to her liking fourth-up. Never comfortable when a brave third over 1350m at Doomben on the heavy surface. Ready to break through. MOTION A NATION (6) wound up strongly on debut from last on the turn when third over 1000m at Casino. Should have come on with that run under the belt and will relish this trip. STARWARD (3) just under a month between runs when faded late for a narrow fourth over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast. Further improved now from the good gate. Will take catching. ZELLWEGER (8) failed to keep up with them early on debut when fifth over 1000m at Ballina. Should appreciate the extra ground this time with Thornton retaining the ride.
